E. W. KRAMER, Appellant, v. Hannah E. FORBES et al., Appellees. No. 7231. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 27, 1933. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Lewis M. Andrews, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal., and Everts, Ewing, Wild So Everts and Dan F. Conway, all of Fresno, Cal., for appellant. Borton So Petrini, of Bakersfield, Cal'., for appellees.

Before SAWTELLE, Circuit Judge, and NORCROSS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
